{
  "text": "under the constraint that the projections Xu i are orthogonal to each other and have unit length, u T i X T Xu i = 1 [CITATION_1] . As it turns out, the projection directions u i are the columns of the matrix U that contains the eigenvectors of C = (X T X) \u22121 X T yy T X. For regression, as in PCR, X is projected onto U, and we work only with the projections. Thus, we minimize ||y \u2212 XU\u03b1|| 2 with respect to \u03b1 and obtain",
